Hurricane "Mitch" Inflicts 28 Dead, Leaves Tens of Thousands of Refugees in Central America
 
San Jose 10-28 (AFP) - Hurricane Mitch, one of the strongest hurricanes of this century, continued its onslaught of Central America where it inflicted 28 dead and left tens of thousands of residents without shelter.

Wind speed retracted today to 200 km an hour after it was 250 km yesterday.

Since last weekend, the hurricane had inflicted 11 dead in Honduras, eight in Nicaragua, six in Costa Rica, two in Guatemala and one in Panama.

Unconfirmed reports said that 14 people were killed in Honduras.
